# Example CLAUDE.md

This is an example of how your project's CLAUDE.md integrates with Canon Memory Claude Rules.
The rules live in `~/.claude/rules/` and are always active. Your CLAUDE.md handles project-specific context.

---

## Project Info

- **Stack**: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase
- **Live URL**: https://your-app.vercel.app
- **Repo**: github.com/your-org/your-project

## Coding Guidelines

- Use Tailwind utility classes, no custom CSS files
- All API routes go in `src/app/api/`
- Use React Query for client-side data fetching
- **Workflow rules**: See `~/.claude/rules/` for verification, plan discipline, debugging, experience evolution, and coding preference rules.

## Deploy

- Auto-deploys via Vercel on push to `main`
- Run `npm run build` before pushing
- Environment variables are in `.env.local` (not committed)

## Key Decisions

- Using Supabase Auth with PKCE flow
- Row Level Security enabled on all tables
- Images stored in Supabase Storage, served via CDN
